%h2 The Bipolar Cycle

%p The psychiatric profession in general views bipolar disorder as abnormalities in the brain which need to be “fixed”. I view bipolar disorder as an extreme manifestation of the above natural cycle.

=render "cycle",
  chunks: Phase.each.collect{|p| "<b>#{p.episode}</b><br />#{p.natural_state.wrap}<p class='left'>#{p.words.ing.capitalize} is easy, but #{p.opposite.words.ing}#{%w|⇗ ⇘ ⇙ ⇖|[p.index]} is hard.</p>".html_safe}

%p I also believe that <em>how</em> it manifests depends on your personality: my mother, her father, and his mother were all bipolar, and they all had wildly different symptoms from me, despite it most probably being caused by the same genes.

%p BipolarType is not an attempt to stop the cycle but instead offers a seatbelt for the roller-coaster ride so you won’t be thrown off during the highs of mania, left behind during the lows of depression, or lost during the transitions.


