%h2 Your BipolarType

%p Your BipolarType is a combination of your Nature (which behaviors are easiest for you based on your physiology, and thus most likely to <em>create</em> an imbalance during a prolonged phase of the cycle) and your Nurture (which behaviors are most important and thus must be preserved <em>despite</em> the imbalance they cause).

%p The goal of BipolarType is <em>balance</em>. That means finding a balance between #{Verb.map(&:nature).and} #{Verb.map(&:episode).and.wrap} and between #{Noun.map(&:nature).and} #{Noun.map(&:episode).and.wrap}. It does not mean treating all four realms equally. It does mean finding balance within each realm.

%p To discover your own BipolarType, start with an unbalanced realm: #{Realm.collect{|r| link_to r.name, r.path}.or.html_safe}, or a compulsive #{link_to 'behavior', behaviors_path}.
